	<h2>Geomancer</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>A caster in tune with the elements, his playstyle and stat focus vary according to element</li>
		<li>main stats to focus on: CON, WIL</li>
		<li>Trained to use magical artifacts as weapons.</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>	
		<h3>Daily</h3>
		<ul>
			<li>Solar Storm – Geomancer channels their energies to create a storm of solar flares that strike at enemies within the surrounding battlefield. For 3 turns, every enemy rolls d20 + CON mod vs Geomancer’s d20 + (2 x WIL mod.) Solar flares that hit do damage equal to the sum of all the Geomancer’s stat mods. This powerful technique is also known as the “Sunny Delight Special” in some circles.</li>
		</ul>	
		
		<h3>Abilities</h3>
		Starting abilities </br>
		<ol style="1">	
			<li>Terran Shield – call forth a shield made of elements from the earth (metal, rock, sand, dirt, etc.) Terran Shield absorbs up to 2 x CON mod.</li>
			<li>Soothing Tide – alleviate burn or toxin, thaw frostbite, cure paralysis, and staunch bleed.</li>  
		</ol>		
		
		Lvl 3 </br>
		<ul>
			<li>Slipstream Scooter – Ride a current of air (Power level x 5 ft.) in any direction. If there is an enemy or an obstacle in your path, roll D20 + Con mod vs. enemy D20 + Con mod to knock down or be knocked down. If equal, both knocked down.</li>
		</ul>
		
		Lvl 5 </br>
		<ul>
			<li>Directed fire – Send a fireball 30ft away or direct a pillar of fire in a 15 x 15ft square in a direction (fixed).  Fireball damage is equal to power level roll. For Pillar, refer to ½ power level roll. Both will add WIL mod to damage.</li>
		</ul>
		
		Lvl 7 </br>	
		<ul>
			<li>Scalding Stream – Release a burst of steam and air in a 15ft line, stopping at the first target/obstacle hit. Damage done equals d# x Power Level + WIL mod.</li>
		</ul>
